# Request Control Tower Rules

Use these rules when working on staffing request dashboards, Request Control Tower, SLA, backlog, fulfillment, cancellation, lifecycle trend, root cause ranking, or related dashboard code.

Before editing:

* Read CLAUDE.md.
* Read .claude/skills/request-control-tower-advisor/SKILL.md.
* Read relevant reference files under .claude/skills/request-control-tower-advisor/references/.

Core rules:

* Never mix หาได้แล้ว with ปิดครบใบขอ.
* Never count cancelled positions as fulfilled.
* Never treat จบงานแล้ว as always equal to ปิดครบใบขอ.
* Never silently treat snapshot inform_qty as exact monthly fulfillment.
* If event date is missing, mark affected metrics as snapshot_fallback.
* Always preserve existing dashboard behavior unless explicitly asked to replace it.
* Prefer parallel layer over direct rewrite.
* Keep old dashboard behind feature flag until verified.
* Always include unit tests for calculation changes.
* Always update 09-editing-map.md if new internal files are added.

Safe architecture:

* parallel calculation layer
* feature flag
* adapter
* read-only API
* backward-compatible types
* preview route
* unit tests
* reconciliation

Core equation:
ยอดค้างต้นงวด + ขอใหม่ - หาได้แล้ว - ยกเลิก = เหลือหา
